social_posts.post_text: What’s better for tired feet and bones than hot food in a warm cafe when it’s cold and misty outside? No Shillong trip of mine is complete without at least one stop at @ml05cafe. Just love the vibes and the food…and when I have the right company it becomes several times more enjoyable 😊 #ljkinmeghalaya

It was only in my last San Francisco trip that I finally went to Hawk Hill, a 923-foot peak in Marin Headlands, located across the Golden Gate Strait. It’s a little out of the way from the city and involves a bit of hiking (pretty easy one) but you would be rewarded with the most amazing Bay area views. And the sunset from here was simply mind blowing. 
I’m letting the pics and videos do the talking here. The last two pics are after sunset, when the lights had come on in the Bay Area and Golden Gate Bridge.

Gontse Gaden Rabgyel Lling Monastery and monastic school at Bomdila. The monastery is popularly referred to as upper gompa by tourists and travelogues. But as I talked to some of the monks there and at what’s popularly called lower gompa, it’s a nomenclature that they are truly unhappy about. I was requested to use the actual names if I don’t mind. So here goes.
It was time for Philosophy class when I visited on a cloudy afternoon. Couldn’t help photograph a few of the samaneras (novice monks) as they headed towards their class.
Remembering the cool climes, valleys and peaks from a couple of weeks ago while sweating it out in humid Mumbai 😅
Today I met the cutest kid I’ve ever seen ❤️❤️

In Kigwema, a traditional Angami tribal village in Nagaland. This is the house of one of the respected families in the village which can be identified by the hornbill beak structure stop the roof. The style and positioning of these are different from what we see atop several buildings in Kohima or Dimapur towns or along the road denoting entry gates to various villages. That’s something a family is allowed to put up as a prestige once it has given a sumptuous feast to the entire village. These houses will have a row of cattle skulls displayed right above the door (see first two pics) that belonged to the animals slaughtered for the feast. 

It’s best to hire a local guide if you want to go slightly offbeat or walk inside traditional villages. They charge around Rs 2500 per day per person if you have your own vehicle. My guide gave lunch and evening tea also in that amount. 

See the video to see inside the village

Mandir, masjid, church and a plateful of the famous Kuttichira biriyani sums up today, my last day in historic Calicut. 

14th century Tali Shiva Temple, 14th century Mishkal Mosque and 16th century Mother of God Cathedral are within a couple of kilometres of each other and have undergone several renovations of the original structures.  Non-Hindus are not allowed inside Tali temple and non-Muslims are not allowed inside Mishkal mosque. As a Kerala Syrian Christian, I could enter only the Cathedral. 

I wrapped up with a late lunch at the legendary Kuttichira Biriyani Centre on Gujarati Street. I’ve no words to describe how mouthwatering the biriyani was! Don’t miss that if you’re ever in Calicut. It’s insanely busy and crowded but if you’re a biriyani lover, I guarantee that’s the place to go to when in Calicut.

We have had a hectic few months moving apartments within the Maximum City post retirement while also renovating our 23-year-old villa in Kochi. Splitting time between two of our beloved cities seemed easy but we hadn’t anticipated the logistics involved in keeping two establishments. Five months on, I think it’s safe to say we’ve managed to find a balance. We still can’t decide which city we like better and I think that’s the best sign 😊
#retiredlife

Off to a wedding reception in a Kasavu that was worn for another wedding last month in Bangalore. Today we put up the smallest Christmas tree we’ve ever used. Trust me it was the most liberating experience as my previous 8 feet and 10 feet trees, while looking super stunning, used to exhaust me by the end of setting them up. In contrast this little one was a joy to set up. 
#retiredlife
Wishing everyone a very Happy Christmas 🎄
Sometimes all you need is some greenery and quiet. #latergram #retiredlife
